Store fewer orphan tx by default, add -maxorphantx option

There is no reason to store thousands of orphan transactions;
normally an orphan's parents will either be broadcast or
mined reasonably quickly.

This pull drops the maximum number of orphans from 10,000 down
to 100, and adds a command-line option (-maxorphantx) that is
just like -maxorphanblocks to override the default.

Author: Peter Todd <pete@petertodd.org>
Date:   Mon Sep 29 03:44:25 2014 -0400

    Replace NOP2 with CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY (BIP65)

    <nLockTime> CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY -> <nLockTime>

    Fails if tx.nLockTime < nLockTime, allowing the funds in a txout to be
    locked until some block height or block time in the future is reached.

    Only the logic and unittests are implemented; this commit does not have
    any actual soft-fork logic in it.

getbestblockhash and time as epoch for ledger

Make proof of stakes valid on spent outputs

When Bitcoin 0.8 was merged the proof of stake check was changed to use
the new CCoin interface to get the transaction and verify the signature.
But the new behavior is different because this interface doesn't return
the outputs that have been spent.

So a node would not accept a proof a stake if the kernel has been spent
in its current chain, whereas this proof could be valid and part of a
new best chain. In a specific scenario the node could be stuck on a
fork.

This commit reverts to the previous behavior based on the complete
transaction (that was already loaded anyway).

The check that the CoinStake inputs are not spent is still done when the
block is connected to the main chain.

Fix the best block duplicate stake handling

The code that removes the best block when its proof of stake is used on
another chain was not able to recover when the removed block was part of
a new best chain.

With these changes the block is no longer marked as invalid and is
temporarily saved in memory so that it can be accepted again if a new
chain is built on top of it.

Change to peercoin's getblock rpc interface to be closer to recent bitcoind
This patch moves the 2nd parameter [txinfo] to the 3rd paramter.
The 2nd parameter of getblock becomes [verbose] which allows the raw getblock output, with full info.
One use case is the bitcore-node server.

This could be a breaking change for Peercoin. In that case,
the [verbose] param could be just added as a 3rd parameter.

events.message: Remove -beta suffix for release
0.6.0 preparation
merge of automake tools

build: Fix boost build on some platforms

When the libpath doesn't line up with the value from config.sub, we don't find
the correct path to boost's libs. This adds a hack to try another path before
giving up.

Should close #3219.
automake fixes

build: ensure the correct strip is used for osx/win32

Conflicts:
	Makefile.am

build: hook up "make deploy" for cross osx builds

Conflicts:
	Makefile.am

fix permissions in application bundle

Use INSTALL_DATA rather than INSTALL for copying non executable files in
OS X application bundle.

Tested by running "all appbundle" make target and trying the resulting
application bundle, host system is OS X 10.9.2 .

build: fix make clean on OSX

Rebased-From: 74df0f5
Rebased-By: Wladimir J. van der Laan <laanwj@gmail.com>
build: Fix 'make deploy' when binaries haven't been built yet

build: fix race in 'make deploy' for windows

The binary builds can clobber eachother, so use a single subdir dependency
instead.

Conflicts:
	Makefile.am

Create the common location for all m4 autotool build scripts, build-aux/m4.

Update .gitignore.

Conflicts:
	.gitignore
	build-aux/m4/bitcoin_find_bdb48.m4
	build-aux/m4/bitcoin_qt.m4
	build-aux/m4/bitcoin_subdir_to_include.m4
	configure.ac

build: add the deploydir target for gitian

This is a helper target that stops just before the creation of the dmg.

Conflicts:
	Makefile.am

build: add a deterministic dmg signer

Conflicts:
	contrib/gitian-descriptors/gitian-osx.yml

build: if cross-compiling for an apple host, locate some additional tools

This should be safe to do for native builds too, but for now it's
specific to cross-builds to avoid possible regressions.

Update obsolete AC macros.

Conflicts:
	configure.ac

qt5: split out qt config and add qt5 support

Qt5 detection is a big ugly mess, but at least we can fence it off.

Conflicts:
	configure.ac
protobuf is not required for peercoin
makefile fixes
qt and mac fixes

build: split the non-gui startup routines into a new file

This will allow each to have its own main(), meaning that we can build a common
base client and simply link in the correct startup object to create the
appropriate binary.
fix moc

osx: make use of the 10.8+ user notification center to display growl like notifications

- if 10.8, use user notification center, if <10.8, use growl

Signed-off-by: Jonas Schnelli <jonas.schnelli@include7.ch>
qt5 fixes
removetransaction rpc call
getbestblockhash implemented
configure: Change --with[out]-qt to --with[out]-gui and add --with[out]-cli and --with[out]-daemon to support more build configurations
missing parts

bitcoin-cli: remove unneeded dependencies (only code movement)

Remove unnecessary dependencies for bitcoin-cli
(leveldb, berkelydb, wallet, RPC server)

Build system changes:
- split libbitcoin.a into libbitcoin_common.a, libbitcoin_server.a and
  libbitcoin_cli.a

Code changes (movement only):
- split up HelpMessage into HelpMessage in init.cpp and HelpMessageCli
  in rpcclient.cpp
- move uiInterface from init.cpp to util.cpp

Split up bitcoinrpc (code movement only)

Split bitcoinrpc up into

- rpcserver: bitcoind RPC server
- rpcclient: bitcoin-cli RPC client
- rpcprotocol: shared common HTTP/JSON-RPC protocol code

One step towards making bitcoin-cli independent from the rest
of the code, and thus a smaller executable that doesn't have to
be linked against leveldb.

This commit only does code movement, there are no functional changes.
extra conflicts
oops

Use boost::asio::deadline_timer for walletpassphrase timeout

New method in bitcoinrpc:  RunLater, that uses a map of deadline
timers to run a function later.

Behavior of walletpassphrase is changed; before, calling
walletpassphrase again before the lock timeout passed
would result in: Error: Wallet is already unlocked.

You would have to call lockwallet before walletpassphrase.

Now: the last walletpassphrase with correct password
wins, and overrides any previous timeout.

Fixes issue# 1961 which was caused by spawning too many threads.

Test plan:

Start with encrypted wallet, password 'foo'
NOTE:
 python -c 'import time; print("%d"%time.time())'
... will tell you current unix timestamp.

Try:

walletpassphrase foo 600
getinfo
EXPECT: unlocked_until is about 10 minutes in the future

walletpassphrase foo 1
sleep 2
sendtoaddress mun74Bvba3B1PF2YkrF4NsgcJwHXXh12LF 11
EXPECT: Error: Please enter the wallet passphrase with walletpassphrase first.

walletpassphrase foo 600
walletpassphrase foo 0
getinfo
EXPECT: wallet is locked (unlocked_until is 0)

walletpassphrase foo 10
walletpassphrase foo 600
getinfo
EXPECT: wallet is unlocked until 10 minutes in future

walletpassphrase foo 60
walletpassphrase bar 600
EXPECT: Error, incorrect passphrase
getinfo
EXPECT: wallet still scheduled to lock 60 seconds from first (successful) walletpassphrase

return newthread

Make it possible to build Bitcoin without wallet

Build logic moves from individual Makefile.am's to include files, which
the main src/Makefile.am includes. This avoids having to manage a gigantic
single Makefile.
